Our national lockdown is being prescribed by mathematical models with inaccuracies that are beginning to rival those of global warming fanatics.
The models don’t work.
He explains the models were wrong from the git-go:"Aside from New York, nationally there’s been no health system crisis.
In fact, to be truly correct there has been a health system crisis, but the crisis is that the hospitals are empty.
Berenson isn’t advocating a hands-off approach to the virus, but what he is advocating is abandoning the Great Pandemic Panic.